         <div>
            <p>RE: WISE WIVES</p>

            <p>This is a delightful treatment of a theme that is rather trifling, but with <choice>
                  <sic>skilful</sic>
                  <corr>skillful</corr>
               </choice> building in continuity will make a bright up-to-the-minute, sophisticated
               drawing room comedy.</p>

            <p>The characterizations are above the average and there is opportunity for some
               excellent comedy in the sort of matinee idol chap with his over-lapping love affairs.
               The other fellow, Jerry, is something of a dub but could be made into a likeable
               fellow no doubt. Madge, though a good characterization, is rather superfluous to the
               story and should be involved in some important way. Toni is mighty well handled.
               There are lots of girls just like her. This is clean-cut, pleasant comedy drama. </p>

         </div>
      </body>
